Unicode multibyte encoding systems.
ISO standard single byte encoding systems.
Special encoding systems. E.g. combinations of encoding
systems.

Windows encoding systems, see

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum CharEncodingType::charEncodingType
 

Enumeration values:
invalidEncodingType 
UTF8  UTF-8 encoding Used for unicode by Linix (NFC).

UTF16_be  UTF-16 encoding, big endian byte order.
UTF16_le  UTF-16 encoding, little endian byte order.

Little endian is more common than big endian.

  • Used for unicode by Windows (NFC?).
UCS2_be  UCS-2 encoding, big endian byte order.
UCS2_le  UCS-2 encoding, little endian byte order.
UCS4_be  UCS-4 encoding, big endian byte order.
UCS4_le  UCS-4 encoding, little endian byte order.
iso8859_1  Latin-1: ASCII + Western European languagers.
iso8859_2  Latin-2: ASCII + Central European languages.
iso8859_3  Latin-3: ASCII + South European languages, Maltese and Esperanto.
iso8859_4  Latin-4: ASCII + Baltic languages.
iso8859_5  ASCII + Slavic languages.
iso8859_6  ASCII + Arabic characters.
iso8859_7  ASCII + Greek characters.
iso8859_8  ASCII + Hebrew characters.
iso8859_9  Latin-5: As Latin-1 but favours Turkish over Icelandic.
iso8859_10  Latin-6: ASCII + Nordic languages, i.e.

Latvian & Inuit & non-Skolt Sami.

iso8859_11  ASCII + Thai support.
iso8859_13  Latin-7: ASCII + Celtic support.
iso8859_14  Latin-8: ASCII + Baltic Rim chars.
iso8859_15  Latin-9: ASCII + Sami support (Finnish).
iso8859_16  Latin-10: As Latin-1 but with euro-sign and accented Finnish & French chars.
UTF8_or_Iso8859_1  Latin-1 or UTF-8 encoding.

Use this when encoding can be eithter of UTF-8 and Latin-1.

windows_1250  Single byte, central Europe.
windows_1251  Single byte, cyrillic.
windows_1252  Single byte, latin 1.
windows_1253  Single byte, greek.
windows_1254  Single byte, turkish.
windows_1255  Single byte, hebrew.
windows_1256  Single byte, arabic.
windows_1257  Single byte, baltic.
windows_1258  Single byte, vietnam.
nbrEncodingTypes  End marker, keep last.
